Tests for the stop-hook mode of `ctx-scan`, which reports stale context but never regenerates it (that is `ctx-run`'s job post-session) and stays silent on a fresh tree.

The hook writes JSON to stdout: a systemMessage describing staleness and a hint to run `ctx-scan --update`, or nothing if the tree is fresh. `stop_hook(&base, &mut out)` is the entry point; it writes to the provided buffer.

`stale_tree_reports_and_never_regenerates` verifies the hook emits a report containing "systemMessage", "stale", and "--update" when the tree lacks a `.ctx` file, and confirms the tree remains stale afterward (no regeneration). `fresh_tree_emits_nothing` seeds a tree with `update_run` using a `StubAgent`, then asserts `stop_hook` produces empty output. `oversized_backlog_hint_includes_approve` creates a tree with `MAX_TARGETS + 1` source files and verifies the hint mentions `--update --approve` to batch-process the backlog.

All tests use `test_dir(label)` to isolate tmpdir paths and `fixture()` to create a minimal src/lib.rs in a clean directory.